IVX CHAT KEYBOARD FAILURE — SAMSUNG BROWSER REAL DEVICE FIX

CURRENT LIVE FAILURE

Production URL:
https://chat.ivxholding.com/home

Real Samsung Android screen recording proves:

- chat page loads;
- conversation history renders;
- user taps the message composer;
- keyboard does not open;
- input does not enter an editable state;
- page remains stuck with the fixed Live Work/composer region.

This is NOT accepted as working.

Do not test only HTTP 200.
Do not test only source code.
Do not claim PASS because the input exists.
Fix and verify actual keyboard opening on the owner Samsung phone.

==================================================
1. REPRODUCE THE EXACT FAILURE
==================================================

Test on:

- Samsung Internet
- Android Chrome
- Expo WebView if used
- portrait mode
- real production URL

Record:

INPUT_ELEMENT=
DISABLED=
READONLY=
CONTENTEDITABLE=
TABINDEX=
POINTER_EVENTS=
Z_INDEX=
FOCUSED_AFTER_TAP=
DOCUMENT_ACTIVE_ELEMENT=
KEYBOARD_VISIBLE=
VISUAL_VIEWPORT_HEIGHT_BEFORE=
VISUAL_VIEWPORT_HEIGHT_AFTER=

Return the first exact reason focus fails.

==================================================
2. AUDIT ALL TAP-BLOCKING OVERLAYS
==================================================

Inspect every element above or around the composer:

- Live Work panel
- floating terminal button
- AI button
- loading overlay
- message delivery overlay
- scroll-to-bottom button
- bottom navigation
- modal backdrop
- transparent absolute containers
- pseudo-elements
- full-screen press handlers

For each return:

ELEMENT
POSITION
Z_INDEX
POINTER_EVENTS
BOUNDING_RECT
OVERLAPS_INPUT
ACTION

Requirements:

- no invisible element may cover the input;
- decorative layers must use pointer-events: none;
- only real buttons may capture taps;
- composer must have the highest required interactive z-index.

==================================================
3. VERIFY THE INPUT IS ACTUALLY EDITABLE
==================================================

The message field must not be:

- disabled while idle;
- permanently readOnly;
- replaced by a display-only div;
- blocked because AI is “working”;
- blocked because an old send state remains active;
- blocked by owner-session loading;
- blocked by message-delivery state.

Required behavior:

- user can type while background work is running;
- sending one message does not permanently disable input;
- failed send restores input;
- loading state does not prevent focus unless intentionally locked;
- disabled state has an explicit visible reason.

Return:

DISABLE_CONDITIONS=
STALE_DISABLE_STATE=
FIX_APPLIED=

==================================================
4. FIX FOCUS LOSS
==================================================

Audit for immediate focus removal caused by:

- onBlur handler;
- route rerender;
- key-based component remount;
- changing input key;
- conditional composer replacement;
- scroll-to-bottom state update;
- message polling;
- realtime subscription updates;
- Live Work updates;
- parent Pressable;
- preventDefault on touch events;
- global click handler;
- modal focus trap.

Requirements:

- input component identity remains stable;
- input ref persists;
- background updates do not remount composer;
- no handler calls blur();
- no event prevents default on the input tap;
- activeElement remains the textarea/input after tap.

Add temporary diagnostic logging:

CHAT_INPUT_POINTER_DOWN
CHAT_INPUT_CLICK
CHAT_INPUT_FOCUS
CHAT_INPUT_BLUR
CHAT_INPUT_REMOUNT
ACTIVE_ELEMENT_CHANGED

Return the exact event sequence before and after the fix.

==================================================
5. SAMSUNG BROWSER KEYBOARD SUPPORT
==================================================

Implement mobile keyboard-safe behavior using:

window.visualViewport

Listen for:

- resize
- scroll

Calculate:

KEYBOARD_HEIGHT =
window.innerHeight - visualViewport.height - visualViewport.offsetTop

Apply keyboard-safe composer positioning.

Requirements:

- composer remains visible above keyboard;
- no fixed element traps the viewport;
- page does not jump;
- input scrolls into view;
- Samsung Browser address bar resize is handled;
- safe-area inset is respected.

Use CSS such as:

height: 100dvh;
min-height: 100svh;
padding-bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom);

Avoid relying only on 100vh.

==================================================
6. FIX FIXED/STICKY COMPOSER LAYOUT
==================================================

Audit the composer container.

Verify:

- position fixed/sticky is intentional;
- bottom offset accounts for navigation;
- z-index is correct;
- overflow ancestors do not clip it;
- transform ancestors do not break fixed positioning;
- keyboard does not place it behind the viewport;
- input remains touchable across its entire width.

Return:

COMPOSER_POSITION=
BOTTOM_OFFSET=
NAV_HEIGHT=
SAFE_AREA=
FINAL_Z_INDEX=
OVERFLOW_ANCESTORS=

==================================================
7. REMOVE GLOBAL TOUCH/CURSOR BLOCKERS
==================================================

Search for:

touch-action: none
user-select: none
pointer-events: none
preventDefault()
stopPropagation()
onTouchStart
onPointerDown
onMouseDown
gesture handlers
drag handlers
swipe handlers

Ensure none blocks normal input activation.

For the text field use:

touch-action: manipulation;
pointer-events: auto;
user-select: text;

==================================================
8. KEYBOARD + SCROLL BEHAVIOR
==================================================

When input receives focus:

1. keyboard opens;
2. composer moves above keyboard;
3. last message remains visible;
4. user can scroll conversation;
5. input is not covered;
6. no blank black gap appears;
7. no duplicate scroll-to-bottom animation;
8. no forced scroll loop;
9. no loss of typed text.

Test with:

- one-line message;
- five-line message;
- long pasted message;
- emoji;
- backspace;
- autocorrect;
- rotate device;
- background/resume.

==================================================
9. SEND FLOW
==================================================

Verify:

- tap input;
- keyboard opens;
- type “Keyboard QA test”;
- send button enables;
- tap send;
- keyboard behavior is predictable;
- message appears once;
- message saves once;
- input clears after confirmed send;
- user can immediately focus and type again;
- failed send preserves draft.

Return:

FOCUS_PASS=
TYPE_PASS=
SEND_PASS=
PERSIST_PASS=
DUPLICATES=
REFOCUS_PASS=
FAILED_SEND_DRAFT_PASS=

==================================================
10. TEST ALL CHAT ENTRY ROUTES
==================================================

Verify keyboard on:

- /home
- /chat
- /chat-room
- IVX Owner AI chat
- public chat
- member chat
- investor chat

If multiple composer implementations exist, consolidate them into one shared,
tested component.

Return:

ROUTE
COMPOSER_FILE
KEYBOARD_OPEN
TYPE
SEND
PASS/FAIL

==================================================
11. REAL DEVICE EVIDENCE
==================================================

Required real-device proof:

- Samsung Internet screen recording;
- Android Chrome screen recording;
- tap input;
- keyboard visibly opens;
- type message;
- send message;
- second message typed immediately;
- rotate portrait/landscape;
- close/reopen browser;
- no regression.

Do not use emulator-only proof.

==================================================
12. DEPLOYMENT
==================================================

After fixing:

- run TypeScript;
- run chat tests;
- build web;
- commit;
- push owner GitHub;
- deploy production;
- invalidate cache;
- hard refresh;
- retest Samsung Browser.

Return:

FILES_CHANGED=
ROOT_CAUSE=
GITHUB_SHA=
FRONTEND_DEPLOY_ID=
LIVE_BUILD_SHA=
CACHE_INVALIDATED=
SAMSUNG_TEST=
CHROME_TEST=

==================================================
FINAL VERDICT
==================================================

Return exactly one:

IVX CHAT KEYBOARD VERIFIED WORKING ON SAMSUNG ANDROID

or

IVX CHAT KEYBOARD STILL BROKEN

Do not return VERIFIED unless:

- keyboard opens on the real Samsung phone;
- input accepts text;
- input does not lose focus immediately;
- composer remains above keyboard;
- message sends;
- message persists;
- second message can be typed;
- no overlay blocks the input;
- no blank gap or layout jump appears;
- production SHA matches GitHub;
- screen recording is provided.

If incomplete, return only:

FAILED_ROUTE:
FAILED_DEVICE:
FAILED_BROWSER:
INPUT_FILE:
OVERLAY_BLOCKING:
FOCUS_EVENT_SEQUENCE:
ACTIVE_ELEMENT:
KEYBOARD_VISIBLE:
ROOT_CAUSE:
FIX_APPLIED:
RETEST_RESULT:
NEXT_EXACT_ACTION:
